The paper deals with system identification for robot platforms, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for producing diverse and valid excitation trajectories suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of cyclic trajectories, which relates to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of GANs for trajectory generation could also be seen as a computer vision (cs.CV) application.
